1. Download Python 3.0 or Higher:
Ensure that you have Python version 3.0 or higher downloaded and installed on your system.

2. Navigate to System Folder:
Open the system folder where you intend to set up the project.

3. Open PowerShell:
Right-click within the system folder while holding the Shift key, and select "Open PowerShell" from the context menu.

4. Install Django:
In the PowerShell terminal, install Django using the following command:
pip install django

5. Install Crispy Forms:
Install Crispy Forms by entering the following command:
pip install django-crispy-forms

6. Install Bootstrap 4:
Install Bootstrap 4 with the following command:
pip install crispy-bootstrap4

7. Run the Server:
Once the necessary programs are downloaded, start the server by running the command:
python manage.py runserver

8. Access the System:
The server will run on your local host. To access the system, open your preferred web browser and enter the following URL:
127.0.0.1:8000

9. Access the Admin Portal:
To access the admin portal, use the URL:
127.0.0.1:8000/admin

10. Admin Portal Login:
Use the following login credentials to access the admin portal:
Username: admin
Password: admin2023

Please follow these instructions carefully to ensure a proper setup of the Python-based system with Django and its associated components. 
If you encounter any issues or require further assistance, do not hesitate to seek support.
